parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can lead to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
and the vehicle is difficult to control when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
and the vehicle is difficult to control when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of lug nuts can cause a wheel to come off while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations from the wheel area
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling in warm weather can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on highways or busy roads.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle loses power and comes to a sudden stop
the engine restarts after a few minutes
difficulty starting the engine after stalling.
